## Writing Functional Requirements

Transform your Needs into formal functional requirements. Each requirement should:
- Describe **what** the object must do, not how it looks
- Be specific enough to test (pass / fail)
- Avoid assuming a particular solution

**Template:** "The [object] must [action / behavior] [measurable condition]."

